configuration.name: preprocessScript

value.expression:
CASE
        WHEN rating = 'G' THEN 'General Audience'
        WHEN rating = 'PG' THEN 'Parental Guidance Suggested'
        WHEN rating = 'PG-13' THEN 'Parents Strongly Cautioned'
        WHEN rating = 'R' THEN 'Restricted'
        WHEN rating = 'NC-17' THEN 'No One 17 and Under Admitted'
        ELSE 'Unrated'
    END

CASE
        WHEN duration LIKE '%min%' THEN CAST(SUBSTRING(duration, 1, POSITION(' min' IN duration)-1) AS INT)
        WHEN duration LIKE '%hr%' THEN 
            CAST(SUBSTRING(duration, 1, POSITION(' hr' IN duration)-1) AS INT) * 60 + 
            CAST(SUBSTRING(duration, POSITION('hr' IN duration)+3, POSITION(' min' IN duration)-POSITION('hr' IN duration)-3) AS INT)
        ELSE 0
    END

configDefinitions.name: columnName
configDefinitions.label: Column
configDefinitions.description: Name of the column to convert. Java regular expressions may also be used to match multiple columns. Column names and patterns are converted to lowercase before matching. If a column matches multiple expressions, the column is converted to the type in the first match in the list.

configDefinitions.name: variantParseType
configDefinitions.label: Type Input
configDefinitions.description: Determines how to parse the input when converting to Variant. If JSON is chosen, applies the parse_json function. If XML is chosen, applies the parse_xml function. If None is chosen, directly casts the input as variant with no parsing.

configDefinitions.name: objectParseType
configDefinitions.label: Type Input
configDefinitions.description: Determines how to parse the input when converting Object (calling the to_object function). If JSON is chosen, applies the parse_json function. If Variant is chosen, applies the to_variant function. If XML is chosen, applies the parse_xml function.
